Theorem \ref{opt_par_rs_theorem} shows only for a large $\kappa$ (small estimation error) and a small $L$ (a sparse-eavesdropper scenario or a moderate SOP constraint), allocating full power to the information signal provides a higher secrecy rate than the AN scheme does, otherwise generating AN is advantageous.
 Since $R_S$ is a concave function of $\xi$, we can efficiently calculate the unique root $\xi_r$ of $\frac{dR_S}{d\xi_r}=0$ in \eqref{drs} using the bisection method.
Substituting $\xi^*$ and $\varrho(\xi^*)$ into \eqref{rs_max} yields $R_S^*$.





























